\end_layout

\begin_layout Subparagraph
Dynamic of the game
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Teo and the child, as before, need to share a sufficiently large space to
 move around.
 With a 
\begin_inset Quotes fld
\end_inset

blindfolded
\begin_inset Quotes frd
\end_inset

 Teo, the game starts and Teo begins explaining to the child the dynamic
 of the game: Teo narrates that the child has an important task to realize
 in which he has to try to guide it (Teo) through a series of points where
 he must go.
 But as Teo cannot see, must be done with the voice.
 Teo prompts the child to answer out loud 
\begin_inset Quotes fld
\end_inset

Teo, here!
\begin_inset Quotes frd
\end_inset

 whenever it asks 
\begin_inset Quotes fld
\end_inset

Where are you?
\begin_inset Quotes frd
\end_inset

.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

A projector will show a sequence of checkpoints that must be followed, identifie
d, for instances, with colored circles distributed around the room.
 After the explanation and the sequence to follow revealed, the game can
 get started.
 
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

The child must move to the corresponding checkpoint and call 
\begin_inset Quotes fld
\end_inset

Teo, here!
\begin_inset Quotes frd
\end_inset

 so Teo could start moving in his direction.
