\end_inset

Whenever Teo arrives to a correct checkpoint, congratulates the child happily
 and prompts him to keep doing a great job.
 When, instead, Teo arrives to an incorrect checkpoint it prompts the child
 to verify if he is where he should be.
 
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

The game ends when Teo reaches the final checkpoint in which Teo happily
 praise the child with a combination of lighting, faces, sound and images
 displayed in the monitor/projector.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subparagraph
Technological Feasibility and requirements.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As this game is an extension of the previous version of Marcopolo, then,
 it depends in the same technological requirements.
 The additional constraints and requirements are the ones stated below.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
In order to allow Teo to be able to recognize the correctness of its position,
 the checkpoints must be identified.
 For instance, using RFID is possible to do this and, therefore, and RFID
 tag reader must added to the hardware infrastructure of Teo.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
A projector and/or a monitor big enough must be available in the room to
 allow the display of information important for the development of the game.
\end_layout

